ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I feel that the PACE_Life research team has provided me with choices and options about exercising regularly (including not exercising regularly).
Notes: 1 = not at all true for me; 4 = somewhat true for me; 7 = very true for me

ElementDescription: I feel the PACE-Life research team understands how I see things with respect to my exercising regularly.
Notes: 1 = not at all true for me; 4 = somewhat true for me; 7 = very true for me

ElementDescription: The PACE-Life research team conveys confidence in my ability to make changes regarding my exercising regularly.

ElementDescription: The PACE-Life research team listens to how I would like to do things regarding my exercising regularly.
Notes: 1 = not at all true for me; 4 = somewhat true for me; 7 = very true for me

ElementDescription: The PACE-Life research team encourages me to ask questions about my exercising.
Notes: 1 = not at all true for me; 4 = somewhat true for me; 7 = very true for me

ElementDescription: The PACE-Life research team tries to understand how I see my exercising before suggesting any changes.
